You can use the the [LazyWsgi](https://github.com/quantmind/pulsar/blob/c8153f9bfdd44a6392815c02e6a4d11ed42e27fe/pulsar/apps/wsgi/handlers.py#L84) in these situations.
```python
from pulsar.apps import wsgi


class Site(wsgi.LazyWsgi):

    def setup(self, environ=None):
        from mymodule import app
        return wsgi.WsgiHandler((wsgi.wait_for_body_middleware,
                                 wsgi.middleware_in_executor(app)))


def server(**kwargs):
    return wsgi.WSGIServer(Site(), **kwargs)


if __name__ == '__main__':  # pragma    nocover
    server().start()
```

From pulsar 2.0 this will be done automatically by pulsar.

